00:00:02.604 --> 00:00:03.638 position:21% line:89% align:start
[singing in Japanese]

00:01:11.706 --> 00:01:12.540 position:21% line:89% align:start
[singing in Japanese]

00:01:25.185 --> 00:01:26.588 position:16% line:89% align:start
[dramatic music playing]

00:01:26.621 --> 00:01:28.255 position:35% line:83% align:start
[narrator]
Tired of being treated

00:01:28.288 --> 00:01:30.157 position:33% line:83% align:start
like a child
by the Nautilus crew,

00:01:30.190 --> 00:01:33.360 position:19% line:83% align:start
Jean set about building
a new aircraft.

00:01:33.393 --> 00:01:36.229 position:19% line:83% align:start
However, he discovered
that he may be mature,

00:01:36.263 --> 00:01:38.165 position:24% line:83% align:start
but he still needs
the help of others

00:01:38.198 --> 00:01:39.266 position:16% line:89% align:start
to accomplish his goals.

00:01:40.267 --> 00:01:42.570 position:19% line:83% align:start
Jean's new craft worked
wonderfully

00:01:42.604 --> 00:01:44.706 position:27% line:83% align:start
and he took Nadia
into the skies.

00:01:44.739 --> 00:01:46.808 position:21% line:89% align:start
During their flight,

00:01:46.841 --> 00:01:48.643 position:35% line:83% align:start
he promised
that he would grow up

00:01:48.676 --> 00:01:50.545 position:24% line:89% align:start
to be her protector

00:01:50.578 --> 00:01:54.281 position:35% line:83% align:start
and the one
who would take her to Africa.

00:01:54.949 --> 00:01:58.820 position:13% line:83% align:start
Will they one day discover
the secret of Blue Water?

00:02:00.320 --> 00:02:01.154 position:16% line:89% align:start
[dramatic music playing]

00:02:04.559 --> 00:02:06.126 position:27% line:89% align:start
[waves crashing]

00:02:15.469 --> 00:02:17.304 position:38% line:89% align:start
[beeping]

00:02:31.819 --> 00:02:34.454 position:27% line:83% align:start
Captain, it seems
to be a British cargo ship.

00:02:34.488 --> 00:02:36.724 position:27% line:83% align:start
They don't appear
to have noticed us yet, sir.

00:02:36.758 --> 00:02:39.794 position:10% line:83% align:start
Maintain our present position
until it has gone.

00:02:39.827 --> 00:02:42.429 position:35% line:83% align:start
-Aye, aye.
-[horn blaring]

00:02:49.771 --> 00:02:52.339 position:27% line:83% align:start
They're leaving.
We're safe for the time being.

00:02:52.372 --> 00:02:53.808 position:33% line:89% align:start
That's right.

00:02:53.841 --> 00:02:55.877 position:13% line:83% align:start
It's been a long time since
we've been so close to land.

00:02:55.910 --> 00:02:58.345 position:35% line:83% align:start
[engineer]
It certainly has.

00:02:58.378 --> 00:03:00.848 position:16% line:83% align:start
I hope the landing party
finds something useful.

00:03:09.791 --> 00:03:12.426 position:27% line:83% align:start
-[birds chirping]
-[indistinct chatter]

00:03:12.459 --> 00:03:14.327 position:44% line:83% align:start
[man]
You missed a spot, ha ha.

00:03:14.361 --> 00:03:16.430 position:21% line:89% align:start
[indistinct chatter]

00:03:16.463 --> 00:03:18.365 position:13% line:83% align:start
[man] Captain, where do you
want me to put these?

00:03:18.398 --> 00:03:19.734 position:21% line:83% align:start
[woman] Honey, honey,
you have to hold my hand.

00:03:19.767 --> 00:03:21.002 position:30% line:89% align:start
[man] Captain?

00:03:21.035 --> 00:03:22.469 position:41% line:83% align:start
[woman]
Honey, hold my hand.

00:03:22.503 --> 00:03:23.805 position:30% line:89% align:start
Don't go away.

00:03:23.838 --> 00:03:25.807 position:21% line:89% align:start
[indistinct chatter]

00:03:28.676 --> 00:03:30.277 position:33% line:89% align:start
[man 1 sighs]

00:03:30.310 --> 00:03:31.378 position:41% line:83% align:start
[man 1]
We don't get much news

00:03:31.411 --> 00:03:32.880 position:7% line:89% align:start
about sea monsters these days.

00:03:32.914 --> 00:03:34.448 position:16% line:89% align:start
And I have to wonder why.

00:03:34.481 --> 00:03:35.983 position:41% line:83% align:start
[man 2]
I hear that the American fleet

00:03:36.017 --> 00:03:38.686 position:16% line:83% align:start
finished off that blasted
menace once and for all.

00:03:38.720 --> 00:03:40.988 position:41% line:83% align:start
[man 3]
Oh. Do you think that's true?

00:03:41.022 --> 00:03:42.355 position:41% line:83% align:start
[man 2]
Yeah, I reckon it is.

00:03:42.389 --> 00:03:45.258 position:27% line:83% align:start
They said it was
over 200 meters long.

00:03:45.292 --> 00:03:47.327 position:41% line:83% align:start
[man 1]
That's one large haul.

00:03:47.360 --> 00:03:49.463 position:24% line:83% align:start
The Americans sure
can pack a lot of power.

00:03:49.496 --> 00:03:50.832 position:41% line:83% align:start
[man 4]
At least we can sail

00:03:50.865 --> 00:03:52.734 position:27% line:83% align:start
the briny depths
once again in safety.

00:03:52.767 --> 00:03:55.268 position:16% line:83% align:start
[man 2] While the scurvy
bugger has picked up pieces

00:03:55.302 --> 00:03:57.404 position:16% line:89% align:start
like crabs and predators.

00:03:57.437 --> 00:03:58.940 position:10% line:83% align:start
-Farewell to the sea monster.
-[man 1] Hear, hear.

00:03:58.973 --> 00:04:00.508 position:38% line:89% align:start
[laughs]

00:04:00.541 --> 00:04:02.476 position:10% line:89% align:start
The Nautilus is popular here.

00:04:02.510 --> 00:04:03.811 position:38% line:89% align:start
Seems so.

00:04:03.845 --> 00:04:06.279 position:16% line:89% align:start
Not a very good feeling.

00:04:06.313 --> 00:04:07.347 position:47% line:89% align:start
No.

00:04:08.516 --> 00:04:09.650 position:47% line:89% align:start
Oh.

00:04:09.684 --> 00:04:10.718 position:24% line:89% align:start
[helmsman] Join us.

00:04:11.853 --> 00:04:13.521 position:16% line:89% align:start
Did you find some leads?

00:04:13.554 --> 00:04:14.989 position:19% line:89% align:start
I didn't find anything.

00:04:15.022 --> 00:04:17.759 position:10% line:83% align:start
The Neo Atlanteans must have
gone completely undercover.

00:04:17.792 --> 00:04:19.761 position:35% line:83% align:start
[helmsman]
As I expected.

00:04:19.794 --> 00:04:21.896 position:16% line:83% align:start
This journal has the last
report I could find.

00:04:24.431 --> 00:04:27.502 position:10% line:83% align:start
The seas have been delivered
from the dreaded savage.

00:04:27.535 --> 00:04:28.736 position:38% line:89% align:start
[scoffs]

00:04:28.770 --> 00:04:29.837 position:30% line:89% align:start
Try as I might,

00:04:29.871 --> 00:04:31.005 position:33% line:83% align:start
there wasn't
any new information

00:04:31.038 --> 00:04:32.707 position:27% line:83% align:start
to be found about
the Garfish sub

00:04:32.740 --> 00:04:34.474 position:19% line:89% align:start
or the Neo Atlanteans.

00:04:34.509 --> 00:04:37.078 position:7% line:83% align:start
Then they've stopped attacking
cargo ships

00:04:37.111 --> 00:04:39.514 position:27% line:83% align:start
in favor of some
new fiendish agenda.

00:04:39.547 --> 00:04:41.381 position:7% line:89% align:start
A construction of a new tower?

00:04:41.414 --> 00:04:42.517 position:35% line:89% align:start
I doubt it.

00:04:42.550 --> 00:04:44.018 position:27% line:83% align:start
They'll probably
attempt something

00:04:44.051 --> 00:04:45.686 position:16% line:83% align:start
that has a better chance
of success.

00:04:45.720 --> 00:04:47.588 position:19% line:89% align:start
But what could that be?

00:04:47.622 --> 00:04:49.791 position:24% line:83% align:start
We were sent ashore
to find that out.

00:04:49.824 --> 00:04:51.526 position:10% line:89% align:start
But what if we find nothing?

00:04:51.726 --> 00:04:53.661 position:16% line:83% align:start
What will the captain say
if we come back empty-handed?

00:04:54.562 --> 00:04:56.564 position:16% line:83% align:start
You should probably worry
more about Electra.

00:04:56.597 --> 00:04:59.901 position:10% line:83% align:start
Hmm, well, we'd definitely be
in some serious trouble.

00:05:01.401 --> 00:05:02.737 position:44% line:83% align:start
[all]
Hmm.

00:05:03.771 --> 00:05:04.906 position:19% line:89% align:start
Here's my report, sir.

00:05:04.939 --> 00:05:06.339 position:41% line:89% align:start
Mm-hmm.

00:05:06.373 --> 00:05:07.942 position:7% line:89% align:start
The Nautilus' present position

00:05:07.975 --> 00:05:10.011 position:19% line:89% align:start
is West 25, North 306.

00:05:10.044 --> 00:05:12.547 position:19% line:83% align:start
Our depth is presently
96 meters

00:05:12.580 --> 00:05:14.347 position:33% line:83% align:start
with the main
and auxiliary engines

00:05:14.381 --> 00:05:15.817 position:24% line:89% align:start
operating smoothly

00:05:15.850 --> 00:05:18.920 position:27% line:83% align:start
and food supplies
adequate for 20 days or more.

00:05:18.953 --> 00:05:20.955 position:35% line:83% align:start
-However...
-Go on.

00:05:20.988 --> 00:05:23.423 position:27% line:83% align:start
Sir, three rounds
of battle repairs

00:05:23.456 --> 00:05:25.927 position:21% line:83% align:start
have left us short of
maintenance materials.

00:05:27.795 --> 00:05:30.665 position:21% line:83% align:start
I strongly recommend
that we return to our base.

00:05:30.698 --> 00:05:31.833 position:41% line:89% align:start
Mm-hmm.

00:05:31.866 --> 00:05:33.835 position:27% line:83% align:start
We'll consider it
after the landing party

00:05:33.868 --> 00:05:34.902 position:16% line:89% align:start
brings back its findings.

00:05:34.936 --> 00:05:35.970 position:38% line:83% align:start
[Electra]
Yes, sir.

00:05:36.971 --> 00:05:38.039 position:38% line:83% align:start
[Sanson]
So now,

00:05:38.072 --> 00:05:39.674 position:13% line:89% align:start
we're apprentice engineers.

00:05:39.707 --> 00:05:41.843 position:30% line:83% align:start
We're gonna get
our suits all dirty.

00:05:41.876 --> 00:05:42.844 position:38% line:83% align:start
[Hanson]
Hmm.

00:05:42.877 --> 00:05:45.046 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Sanson] We've certainly
been to a lot of places.

00:05:45.079 --> 00:05:46.113 position:38% line:83% align:start
[Hanson]
Mm-hmm.

00:05:46.147 --> 00:05:48.783 position:24% line:83% align:start
Europe must be far,
far away by now.

00:05:50.151 --> 00:05:52.587 position:21% line:83% align:start
I wonder where we are
at this very moment.

00:05:52.620 --> 00:05:56.057 position:10% line:83% align:start
I have no map and no compass,
so I have no idea.

00:05:56.991 --> 00:05:58.526 position:41% line:89% align:start
I know.

00:05:58.559 --> 00:06:00.094 position:24% line:83% align:start
From the stars that
we saw last night,

00:06:00.127 --> 00:06:01.996 position:7% line:89% align:start
I'd say we're pretty far south.

00:06:03.463 --> 00:06:04.497 position:35% line:89% align:start
South, eh?

00:06:05.498 --> 00:06:08.002 position:19% line:83% align:start
I wonder how far south
the captain's sailing.

00:06:10.137 --> 00:06:11.505 position:30% line:89% align:start
[buzzer buzzes]

00:06:11.539 --> 00:06:13.174 position:41% line:83% align:start
[Nemo]
Attention, all hands.

00:06:13.207 --> 00:06:17.178 position:16% line:83% align:start
We are setting course for
Antarctica to take on supplies.

00:06:17.211 --> 00:06:19.614 position:41% line:83% align:start
[both]
We're going where?

00:06:19.647 --> 00:06:20.480 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:06:28.656 --> 00:06:29.489 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:06:30.892 --> 00:06:32.093 position:16% line:89% align:start
What on earth are these?

00:06:32.126 --> 00:06:33.794 position:27% line:89% align:start
Arctic clothing.

00:06:33.828 --> 00:06:35.796 position:30% line:89% align:start
Arctic clothes?

00:06:35.830 --> 00:06:37.732 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Electra] Yes, it will protect
you from the extreme cold.

00:06:38.699 --> 00:06:39.934 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hmm.

00:06:40.902 --> 00:06:42.003 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hmm.

00:06:43.170 --> 00:06:44.972 position:21% line:89% align:start
This won't do at all.

00:06:45.006 --> 00:06:47.074 position:13% line:83% align:start
No one should have to wear
such dowdy clothes.

00:06:48.576 --> 00:06:50.211 position:30% line:89% align:start
That they are.

00:06:50.244 --> 00:06:52.980 position:13% line:83% align:start
I could never allow Captain
Nemo to see me

00:06:53.014 --> 00:06:55.683 position:13% line:83% align:start
in something so inherently
unflattering.

00:06:55.716 --> 00:06:56.851 position:35% line:83% align:start
-[growling]
-Mm-hmm.

00:06:56.884 --> 00:06:57.952 position:30% line:89% align:start
What was that?

00:06:57.985 --> 00:06:59.854 position:41% line:89% align:start
Uh-oh.

00:07:01.722 --> 00:07:04.025 position:27% line:83% align:start
So why do we need
to dress for cold weather?

00:07:05.526 --> 00:07:06.894 position:7% line:89% align:start
We are going to the South Pole.

00:07:06.928 --> 00:07:08.529 position:24% line:89% align:start
We're going where?

00:07:08.562 --> 00:07:10.798 position:38% line:83% align:start
[Sanson]
You've got to be kidding.

00:07:10.831 --> 00:07:12.465 position:21% line:89% align:start
Whose idea was that?

00:07:12.499 --> 00:07:15.503 position:19% line:83% align:start
Nemo has really lost it
this time.

00:07:15.536 --> 00:07:17.004 position:19% line:89% align:start
His home port is there.

00:07:17.038 --> 00:07:18.072 position:41% line:89% align:start
Ah-hah.

00:07:18.105 --> 00:07:19.607 position:30% line:89% align:start
His home port?

00:07:19.640 --> 00:07:21.075 position:21% line:83% align:start
What kind of a madman
builds a port

00:07:21.108 --> 00:07:22.643 position:16% line:89% align:start
in a wasteland like that?

00:07:22.677 --> 00:07:25.546 position:24% line:83% align:start
Why does he always
have to do things the hard way?

00:07:25.579 --> 00:07:26.948 position:21% line:89% align:start
Can you tell me that?

00:07:26.981 --> 00:07:29.116 position:27% line:83% align:start
Is the South Pole
really that terrible?

00:07:30.284 --> 00:07:33.754 position:19% line:83% align:start
It's so detestable that
every captain in his right mind

00:07:33.788 --> 00:07:35.089 position:13% line:89% align:start
steers clear of the place.

00:07:35.122 --> 00:07:37.792 position:16% line:89% align:start
The wind has spiky teeth.

00:07:38.793 --> 00:07:41.228 position:19% line:89% align:start
The ice fossilizes you.

00:07:41.963 --> 00:07:44.198 position:16% line:83% align:start
And when you lament your
impending death,

00:07:44.231 --> 00:07:46.567 position:27% line:83% align:start
your tears freeze
to your face.

00:07:46.600 --> 00:07:48.836 position:30% line:83% align:start
It is no place
for civilized man.

00:07:50.538 --> 00:07:52.139 position:21% line:89% align:start
It's really that bad?

00:07:52.173 --> 00:07:55.843 position:16% line:83% align:start
Many courageous explorers
have tried to reach the Pole,

00:07:55.876 --> 00:07:58.112 position:19% line:83% align:start
and they all have been
killed trying.

00:07:58.145 --> 00:08:00.614 position:27% line:83% align:start
I don't care how
advanced the ship is.

00:08:00.648 --> 00:08:03.084 position:16% line:83% align:start
They haven't built a ship
that could survive down there.

00:08:04.819 --> 00:08:06.854 position:24% line:89% align:start
Jean, is this true?

00:08:06.887 --> 00:08:08.923 position:33% line:89% align:start
Uh-huh. Huh?

00:08:08.956 --> 00:08:10.658 position:19% line:89% align:start
I'm sure we'll be fine.

00:08:11.926 --> 00:08:14.562 position:33% line:83% align:start
Oh, boy, huh.
The South Pole,

00:08:14.595 --> 00:08:16.230 position:33% line:89% align:start
I can't wait.

00:08:16.263 --> 00:08:18.532 position:30% line:89% align:start
We're so lucky.

00:08:18.566 --> 00:08:19.734 position:30% line:89% align:start
The South Pole?

00:08:19.767 --> 00:08:21.535 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yes.

00:08:21.569 --> 00:08:23.237 position:16% line:83% align:start
You've been there before,
so what kind of a place is it?

00:08:25.806 --> 00:08:27.108 position:44% line:89% align:start
Um...

00:08:27.141 --> 00:08:29.910 position:10% line:83% align:start
Well, it's the place our base
is located.

00:08:29.944 --> 00:08:30.845 position:41% line:89% align:start
Mm-hmm.

00:08:33.247 --> 00:08:35.016 position:7% line:89% align:start
So what kind of a place is it?

00:08:35.049 --> 00:08:36.617 position:24% line:89% align:start
How can I put this?

00:08:37.284 --> 00:08:38.486 position:5% line:89% align:start
It's where the main base is.

00:08:39.820 --> 00:08:41.989 position:27% line:89% align:start
[inhaling deeply]

00:08:42.690 --> 00:08:43.524 position:38% line:89% align:start
[exhales]

00:08:45.326 --> 00:08:47.995 position:30% line:83% align:start
The South Pole,
where the main base is?

00:08:48.029 --> 00:08:49.964 position:10% line:89% align:start
It's where the main base is.

00:08:49.997 --> 00:08:51.966 position:19% line:89% align:start
Our main base is there.

00:08:53.100 --> 00:08:55.136 position:21% line:89% align:start
What, the South Pole?

00:08:55.169 --> 00:08:56.871 position:27% line:83% align:start
Yes. What kind of
a place is it?

00:08:58.039 --> 00:09:00.841 position:16% line:83% align:start
Let's see. It's where the
Nautilus' main base was built.

00:09:00.875 --> 00:09:01.909 position:38% line:89% align:start
[groans]

00:09:03.210 --> 00:09:05.179 position:24% line:83% align:start
-What's the matter?
-I don't know.

00:09:05.212 --> 00:09:06.847 position:27% line:83% align:start
Why does everyone
say the same thing?

00:09:07.848 --> 00:09:10.317 position:30% line:83% align:start
Well, I suppose
no one wants to ruin

00:09:10.351 --> 00:09:12.319 position:7% line:89% align:start
the surprise in store for you.

00:09:13.854 --> 00:09:16.023 position:7% line:83% align:start
Oh, I guess I'll just go ahead
and show you.

00:09:16.057 --> 00:09:17.658 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yes.

00:09:19.994 --> 00:09:21.162 position:47% line:89% align:start
Ah.

00:09:22.063 --> 00:09:23.864 position:27% line:89% align:start
It's like magic.

00:09:23.898 --> 00:09:25.332 position:27% line:89% align:start
Not quite, Nadia.

00:09:25.366 --> 00:09:26.801 position:21% line:89% align:start
It's merely science.

00:09:26.834 --> 00:09:28.602 position:41% line:83% align:start
[Jean]
This is amazing.

00:09:28.636 --> 00:09:31.772 position:19% line:83% align:start
I wonder how it works,
a magic lantern?

00:09:31.806 --> 00:09:33.040 position:38% line:83% align:start
[Electra]
The image is created

00:09:33.074 --> 00:09:34.742 position:19% line:89% align:start
by an electronic brain

00:09:34.775 --> 00:09:37.978 position:24% line:83% align:start
and then projected
using magnets and electricity.

00:09:38.012 --> 00:09:40.881 position:7% line:89% align:start
Oh, what's an electronic brain?

00:09:40.915 --> 00:09:43.984 position:19% line:83% align:start
To put it very simply,
it's a machine that can think.

00:09:44.018 --> 00:09:46.120 position:13% line:83% align:start
I'll explain the details to
you later.

00:09:47.088 --> 00:09:48.856 position:21% line:83% align:start
Would you like to see
the South Pole, Jean?

00:09:48.889 --> 00:09:49.924 position:44% line:89% align:start
Sure.

00:09:52.927 --> 00:09:54.929 position:24% line:89% align:start
That is Antarctica.

00:09:54.962 --> 00:09:57.731 position:30% line:89% align:start
Oh, fantastic.

00:09:57.765 --> 00:09:59.733 position:7% line:89% align:start
It shows the actual shoreline.

00:09:59.767 --> 00:10:01.335 position:13% line:89% align:start
What's so great about that?

00:10:01.368 --> 00:10:04.405 position:27% line:83% align:start
Since Antarctica
is completely covered with ice,

00:10:04.438 --> 00:10:07.641 position:21% line:83% align:start
no one knows exactly
where the edge of the land is.

00:10:07.675 --> 00:10:10.878 position:19% line:83% align:start
But this ship has a map
that details it precisely.

00:10:11.879 --> 00:10:13.080 position:35% line:89% align:start
Incredible.

00:10:14.115 --> 00:10:16.383 position:7% line:89% align:start
Explain to me how you drew it.

00:10:16.417 --> 00:10:18.419 position:24% line:83% align:start
It wasn't necessary
since the information

00:10:18.452 --> 00:10:21.355 position:30% line:83% align:start
was already in
the ship's databank.

00:10:21.388 --> 00:10:23.290 position:19% line:83% align:start
-Then who put it there?
-[gasps]

00:10:23.858 --> 00:10:24.925 position:27% line:89% align:start
Well, that is a--

00:10:25.793 --> 00:10:27.061 position:41% line:89% align:start
A what?

00:10:27.094 --> 00:10:28.863 position:38% line:89% align:start
A secret.

00:10:29.730 --> 00:10:31.765 position:21% line:89% align:start
Aw, that's not fair.

00:10:32.867 --> 00:10:34.768 position:10% line:89% align:start
And what does this mark mean?

00:10:34.802 --> 00:10:37.204 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Electra] That's where
the base is located.

00:10:37.238 --> 00:10:41.175 position:7% line:83% align:start
What? How can we possibly sail
to the middle of a continent?

00:10:41.208 --> 00:10:43.310 position:30% line:83% align:start
-Must we walk?
-[gasps]

00:10:43.344 --> 00:10:46.714 position:19% line:83% align:start
[laughs] The ship will
take us right to it.

00:10:46.747 --> 00:10:49.049 position:21% line:89% align:start
Huh? But how can it?

00:10:49.083 --> 00:10:51.051 position:27% line:89% align:start
That, too, is a--

00:10:51.085 --> 00:10:52.119 position:41% line:89% align:start
A what?

00:10:52.153 --> 00:10:54.255 position:38% line:89% align:start
A secret.

00:10:54.288 --> 00:10:55.956 position:16% line:89% align:start
Oh, I should have known.

00:10:55.990 --> 00:10:59.460 position:33% line:89% align:start
[they laugh]

00:10:59.493 --> 00:11:01.295 position:13% line:89% align:start
You're such a dunce, Jean.

00:11:01.328 --> 00:11:05.199 position:16% line:89% align:start
â™ª The Secret Blue Water

00:11:09.403 --> 00:11:11.772 position:27% line:89% align:start
[waves crashing]

00:11:19.046 --> 00:11:21.815 position:13% line:83% align:start
[sonar] No targets sighted
within 20 kilometers.

00:11:21.849 --> 00:11:23.717 position:38% line:83% align:start
[Electra]
No evidence of jamming devices.

00:11:23.751 --> 00:11:25.986 position:35% line:83% align:start
[engineer]
Activating air compressor.

00:11:26.020 --> 00:11:28.088 position:24% line:83% align:start
We are now entering
the Antarctic zone.

00:11:28.122 --> 00:11:30.958 position:16% line:89% align:start
[dramatic music playing]

00:11:34.762 --> 00:11:37.131 position:21% line:83% align:start
We should be arriving
very soon.

00:11:37.164 --> 00:11:39.166 position:13% line:83% align:start
That's as long as the ship
doesn't hit an iceberg

00:11:39.200 --> 00:11:40.301 position:19% line:89% align:start
and implode, of course.

00:11:40.334 --> 00:11:42.336 position:30% line:83% align:start
-[metal thuds]
-Huh?

00:11:42.369 --> 00:11:44.238 position:41% line:83% align:start
[gasps]
What are those noises?

00:11:47.208 --> 00:11:50.110 position:16% line:83% align:start
We are encountering some
relatively small ice floes.

00:11:50.144 --> 00:11:52.980 position:16% line:89% align:start
[dramatic music playing]

00:11:55.849 --> 00:11:58.319 position:35% line:83% align:start
[helmsman]
Obstacle sighted dead ahead.

00:12:04.124 --> 00:12:06.827 position:24% line:83% align:start
There are ice floes
about five meters in thickness.

00:12:07.828 --> 00:12:10.030 position:38% line:83% align:start
-Captain?
-Compressed air status?

00:12:10.064 --> 00:12:13.334 position:33% line:83% align:start
All cylinders
are full up to 48.

00:12:13.367 --> 00:12:14.868 position:13% line:89% align:start
Two minutes to full status.

00:12:14.902 --> 00:12:16.470 position:24% line:83% align:start
We'll submerge upon
completion.

00:12:16.504 --> 00:12:17.338 position:44% line:89% align:start
Aye.

00:12:19.006 --> 00:12:20.941 position:24% line:83% align:start
We finally make it
to the South Pole

00:12:20.975 --> 00:12:22.876 position:16% line:83% align:start
and they tell us we can't
leave the ship.

00:12:22.910 --> 00:12:25.547 position:13% line:83% align:start
Oh, well, at least we won't
catch a cold.

00:12:25.580 --> 00:12:27.815 position:19% line:89% align:start
But I wanted to see it.

00:12:27.848 --> 00:12:29.483 position:30% line:89% align:start
[buzzer buzzes]

00:12:29.517 --> 00:12:31.285 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Electra] All hands,
prepare to submerge,

00:12:31.318 --> 00:12:33.187 position:19% line:89% align:start
report to workstations.

00:12:33.220 --> 00:12:36.390 position:41% line:83% align:start
[sighs]
I'm going up to the bridge.

00:12:38.025 --> 00:12:40.060 position:38% line:89% align:start
[beeping]

00:12:47.602 --> 00:12:49.870 position:13% line:89% align:start
Diving systems are nominal.

00:12:49.903 --> 00:12:52.406 position:30% line:83% align:start
Ballast normal,
depth is 60 meters.

00:12:52.439 --> 00:12:54.008 position:33% line:83% align:start
-[door opens]
-[gasps]

00:12:54.908 --> 00:12:57.344 position:38% line:89% align:start
[laughs]

00:13:03.384 --> 00:13:05.919 position:33% line:83% align:start
Large iceberg
between 11:00 and 2:00.

00:13:05.953 --> 00:13:07.488 position:10% line:89% align:start
Thirty degrees to starboard.

00:13:07.522 --> 00:13:08.556 position:24% line:89% align:start
Aye, aye, captain.

00:13:15.929 --> 00:13:18.032 position:27% line:89% align:start
Wow, it's so big.

00:13:22.970 --> 00:13:25.205 position:24% line:83% align:start
Heading maintained
at 80 meters.

00:13:31.412 --> 00:13:32.880 position:41% line:83% align:start
[sonar]
This is odd.

00:13:32.913 --> 00:13:34.081 position:21% line:89% align:start
The water temperature

00:13:34.114 --> 00:13:35.382 position:19% line:89% align:start
is over seven degrees.

00:13:35.416 --> 00:13:37.117 position:19% line:89% align:start
And look at the seabed.

00:13:37.151 --> 00:13:39.987 position:13% line:89% align:start
[suspenseful music playing]

00:13:42.156 --> 00:13:44.258 position:21% line:83% align:start
-[sonar] What the...
-[helmsman] What happened here?

00:13:45.560 --> 00:13:46.894 position:35% line:83% align:start
[engineer]
This is terrible.

00:13:47.562 --> 00:13:50.264 position:27% line:83% align:start
It's a graveyard
for the animals of the sea.

00:13:50.297 --> 00:13:53.000 position:30% line:83% align:start
Run an analysis
of the water's composition.

00:13:53.033 --> 00:13:53.934 position:44% line:89% align:start
Aye.

00:13:58.005 --> 00:13:59.973 position:13% line:89% align:start
Magnetic field is unstable.

00:14:00.007 --> 00:14:02.577 position:30% line:83% align:start
Carbon dioxide,
hydrogen sulfide,

00:14:02.610 --> 00:14:06.581 position:13% line:83% align:start
and heavy metal ion content
is 200 times normal, sir.

00:14:06.614 --> 00:14:09.483 position:24% line:89% align:start
Hmm, as I thought.

00:14:09.517 --> 00:14:12.086 position:35% line:89% align:start
[explosion]

00:14:17.625 --> 00:14:18.660 position:33% line:89% align:start
Oh, dear God.

00:14:22.530 --> 00:14:24.331 position:38% line:89% align:start
Oh, dear.

00:14:24.365 --> 00:14:26.634 position:13% line:83% align:start
I thought all the volcanoes
around here were dormant.

00:14:26.668 --> 00:14:29.970 position:13% line:83% align:start
Mother Nature always hides
an ace up her sleeve.

00:14:30.003 --> 00:14:31.138 position:21% line:89% align:start
And that's the truth.

00:14:36.143 --> 00:14:37.945 position:33% line:89% align:start
Sir, orders.

00:14:37.978 --> 00:14:40.047 position:35% line:83% align:start
Go around,
it's all that we can do.

00:14:40.080 --> 00:14:41.215 position:44% line:89% align:start
Aye.

00:14:48.222 --> 00:14:50.658 position:10% line:89% align:start
What was all that commotion?

00:14:50.692 --> 00:14:53.160 position:30% line:83% align:start
We sailed past
an underwater volcano.

00:14:53.193 --> 00:14:55.195 position:38% line:83% align:start
-Volcano?
-Mm-hmm.

00:14:55.229 --> 00:14:57.197 position:24% line:83% align:start
There are volcanoes
under the sea?

00:14:57.231 --> 00:14:58.298 position:41% line:89% align:start
Mm-hmm.

00:14:58.332 --> 00:15:00.234 position:38% line:83% align:start
-Oh, my.
-Mm-hmm.

00:15:00.267 --> 00:15:02.136 position:21% line:83% align:start
I'm starting to think
Sanson was right for once.

00:15:07.107 --> 00:15:10.144 position:13% line:83% align:start
Current depth is 160 meters
and holding.

00:15:12.079 --> 00:15:14.448 position:24% line:83% align:start
Unidentified object
approaching.

00:15:14.481 --> 00:15:17.117 position:30% line:83% align:start
It's heading in
from 11:00, sir.

00:15:17.151 --> 00:15:19.153 position:21% line:83% align:start
Relative approaching
speed is 60 knots.

00:15:19.186 --> 00:15:20.688 position:38% line:83% align:start
[Electra]
That couldn't be the Garfish.

00:15:20.722 --> 00:15:23.023 position:13% line:89% align:start
Ten seconds to identify it.

00:15:23.056 --> 00:15:24.191 position:38% line:89% align:start
Aye, sir.

00:15:27.729 --> 00:15:30.431 position:16% line:83% align:start
The Garfish could create
a magnetic response.

00:15:30.464 --> 00:15:31.699 position:33% line:89% align:start
This doesn't.

00:15:33.768 --> 00:15:35.369 position:19% line:89% align:start
Then, what could it be?

00:15:35.402 --> 00:15:37.204 position:35% line:83% align:start
[engineer]
I have no idea.

00:15:37.237 --> 00:15:38.606 position:35% line:83% align:start
[navigator]
What shall we do?

00:15:38.640 --> 00:15:39.973 position:38% line:83% align:start
[Electra]
Captain Nemo.

00:15:42.510 --> 00:15:44.211 position:19% line:89% align:start
Sound general quarters.

00:15:44.244 --> 00:15:46.346 position:30% line:89% align:start
Aye. All hands,

00:15:46.380 --> 00:15:48.550 position:13% line:89% align:start
report to general quarters.

00:15:48.583 --> 00:15:50.518 position:24% line:89% align:start
Prepare for attack.

00:15:50.552 --> 00:15:52.720 position:16% line:89% align:start
Prepare for what attack?

00:15:52.754 --> 00:15:54.756 position:19% line:83% align:start
I thought he said that
nothing could survive

00:15:54.789 --> 00:15:56.256 position:19% line:89% align:start
in these frigid waters.

00:15:56.290 --> 00:15:59.293 position:13% line:89% align:start
[suspenseful music playing]

00:15:59.326 --> 00:16:02.396 position:30% line:83% align:start
Incoming object
has locked on to our position.

00:16:06.534 --> 00:16:08.035 position:19% line:89% align:start
Closing at 600 meters.

00:16:08.068 --> 00:16:09.637 position:19% line:83% align:start
Commence vertical dive,
on the double.

00:16:18.445 --> 00:16:20.715 position:24% line:83% align:start
-Did you see that?
-Sure did.

00:16:20.748 --> 00:16:22.316 position:24% line:83% align:start
That was definitely
no submarine.

00:16:23.450 --> 00:16:24.619 position:33% line:89% align:start
It was alive.

00:16:24.652 --> 00:16:26.453 position:10% line:89% align:start
It looked like a giant squid.

00:16:26.487 --> 00:16:30.324 position:21% line:83% align:start
There's ice above us
and squids below us.

00:16:30.357 --> 00:16:32.292 position:16% line:89% align:start
Could this be any worse?

00:16:32.326 --> 00:16:33.427 position:38% line:89% align:start
[beeping]

00:16:42.336 --> 00:16:44.271 position:35% line:89% align:start
[explosion]

00:16:48.108 --> 00:16:50.512 position:10% line:89% align:start
That sideswiped us, but why?

00:16:50.545 --> 00:16:51.613 position:47% line:89% align:start
Oh.

00:16:52.614 --> 00:16:55.282 position:19% line:83% align:start
An indigenous creature
might come to believe

00:16:55.315 --> 00:16:56.618 position:21% line:83% align:start
that we are invading
its territory.

00:17:03.290 --> 00:17:05.192 position:21% line:83% align:start
It's turned around on
the starboard side.

00:17:05.225 --> 00:17:06.828 position:13% line:89% align:start
Evasive action, do it now.

00:17:06.861 --> 00:17:09.162 position:13% line:83% align:start
Engines are at full speed.
Turn her hard to port.

00:17:13.535 --> 00:17:15.469 position:38% line:83% align:start
No good,
it'll hit us head on.

00:17:15.503 --> 00:17:17.137 position:7% line:89% align:start
All hands brace for collision.

00:17:23.745 --> 00:17:25.680 position:38% line:83% align:start
-[gasps]
-What is going on?

00:17:38.492 --> 00:17:40.795 position:33% line:83% align:start
-It can't be.
-A shellfish.

00:17:40.828 --> 00:17:43.397 position:27% line:83% align:start
This one existed
millions of years ago.

00:17:43.430 --> 00:17:44.264 position:21% line:89% align:start
And it's still alive.

00:17:49.169 --> 00:17:50.705 position:13% line:89% align:start
That thing is crushing us.

00:17:50.738 --> 00:17:53.240 position:19% line:83% align:start
Our weapons are useless
against it.

00:17:53.273 --> 00:17:55.275 position:30% line:83% align:start
[Nemo] With it
attached to the hull? Yes.

00:17:56.844 --> 00:17:59.681 position:13% line:83% align:start
[sonar] It's even cracking
the reinforced textite.

00:17:59.714 --> 00:18:01.348 position:13% line:89% align:start
Close the armored shutters.

00:18:01.381 --> 00:18:02.517 position:44% line:89% align:start
Aye.

00:18:09.591 --> 00:18:11.391 position:33% line:89% align:start
Come on, go.

00:18:11.425 --> 00:18:12.627 position:35% line:89% align:start
Of course.

00:18:12.860 --> 00:18:14.662 position:24% line:83% align:start
What if we directed
a high voltage current

00:18:14.696 --> 00:18:16.363 position:16% line:83% align:start
through the ship's hull,
captain?

00:18:16.396 --> 00:18:18.365 position:7% line:83% align:start
[both] Hey, the kid might have
something there.

00:18:19.601 --> 00:18:21.569 position:19% line:89% align:start
First Officer, try it.

00:18:22.336 --> 00:18:23.571 position:44% line:89% align:start
Aye.

00:18:40.888 --> 00:18:43.290 position:16% line:89% align:start
Look at this. Do you see?

00:18:43.323 --> 00:18:45.593 position:24% line:83% align:start
It's the battle of
the Nautiluses.

00:18:45.627 --> 00:18:46.828 position:24% line:89% align:start
What an awful mess.

00:18:49.229 --> 00:18:50.765 position:19% line:83% align:start
-Increase the voltage.
-Aye.

00:18:59.574 --> 00:19:00.875 position:41% line:83% align:start
[both]
Let go!

00:19:03.611 --> 00:19:06.380 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Nemo] Engines to full power,
begin vertical climb.

00:19:06.413 --> 00:19:07.715 position:19% line:89% align:start
We're under an iceberg.

00:19:07.749 --> 00:19:09.851 position:33% line:83% align:start
I know that.
We are going to ram into it.

00:19:09.884 --> 00:19:10.785 position:38% line:89% align:start
Aye, aye.

00:19:26.801 --> 00:19:29.302 position:24% line:83% align:start
It's holding tight,
amazing power.

00:19:29.336 --> 00:19:30.905 position:19% line:83% align:start
I'd rather be fighting
the Garfish.

00:19:34.542 --> 00:19:36.878 position:13% line:83% align:start
The bridge can't withstand
this kind of pressure.

00:19:41.783 --> 00:19:44.686 position:27% line:83% align:start
Hard to starboard
with heading 107.

00:19:44.719 --> 00:19:46.788 position:33% line:83% align:start
But, Captain,
that's back toward the volcano.

00:19:46.821 --> 00:19:49.356 position:27% line:89% align:start
I know that, 107.

00:19:49.389 --> 00:19:50.357 position:44% line:89% align:start
Aye.

00:19:53.895 --> 00:19:56.931 position:16% line:89% align:start
[dramatic music playing]

00:20:12.947 --> 00:20:14.347 position:35% line:89% align:start
Incredible.

00:20:16.651 --> 00:20:18.920 position:27% line:83% align:start
Steady, steer us
into the crater.

00:20:18.953 --> 00:20:21.656 position:27% line:83% align:start
Captain, the heat
will destroy the ship, sir.

00:20:23.825 --> 00:20:26.393 position:21% line:83% align:start
We are out of options
at this point.

00:20:26.426 --> 00:20:27.494 position:27% line:89% align:start
We must do this.

00:20:32.332 --> 00:20:34.502 position:16% line:83% align:start
Purge all compressed air
from tanks one through thirty.

00:20:39.974 --> 00:20:41.642 position:24% line:89% align:start
Purge is complete.

00:20:41.676 --> 00:20:42.810 position:30% line:89% align:start
We're going in.

00:20:53.487 --> 00:20:55.690 position:38% line:83% align:start
-Status?
-It's still holding on.

00:20:58.893 --> 00:21:00.728 position:30% line:83% align:start
Steer the ship
as close as you can

00:21:00.762 --> 00:21:01.996 position:16% line:89% align:start
to the crater, Helmsman.

00:21:02.029 --> 00:21:02.997 position:38% line:89% align:start
Aye, aye.

00:21:08.069 --> 00:21:09.670 position:7% line:89% align:start
That thing has nerves of steel.

00:21:09.704 --> 00:21:12.707 position:21% line:83% align:start
External temperature
is approaching 1,200 degrees.

00:21:13.574 --> 00:21:14.675 position:30% line:89% align:start
[King panting]

00:21:14.709 --> 00:21:16.077 position:33% line:83% align:start
It feels like
we're burning up here.

00:21:16.110 --> 00:21:18.546 position:30% line:83% align:start
The South Pole
needs to make up its mind.

00:21:24.619 --> 00:21:27.320 position:13% line:83% align:start
How long can it stay alive
in this heat?

00:21:27.354 --> 00:21:28.556 position:30% line:89% align:start
It's a monster.

00:21:34.595 --> 00:21:36.329 position:33% line:83% align:start
We can't take
much more of this, sir.

00:21:36.363 --> 00:21:38.065 position:38% line:89% align:start
Captain?

00:21:38.099 --> 00:21:40.768 position:30% line:83% align:start
If it is alive,
it will have to let go.

00:21:47.041 --> 00:21:49.076 position:33% line:89% align:start
[screeching]

00:21:50.011 --> 00:21:51.813 position:35% line:83% align:start
-We did it.
-[Jean cheering]

00:21:52.914 --> 00:21:55.448 position:10% line:89% align:start
[monster screeching raspily]

00:22:04.091 --> 00:22:05.726 position:30% line:89% align:start
We were lucky.

00:22:05.760 --> 00:22:06.994 position:35% line:89% align:start
So was it.

00:22:07.028 --> 00:22:09.362 position:19% line:83% align:start
It came close to being
dropped into hot lava.

00:22:09.396 --> 00:22:11.398 position:30% line:83% align:start
I think it made
the right choice.

00:22:11.431 --> 00:22:14.569 position:10% line:83% align:start
I can't believe such a thing
still exists.

00:22:14.602 --> 00:22:16.504 position:13% line:83% align:start
It seems to me that nature
often keeps

00:22:16.537 --> 00:22:17.939 position:24% line:83% align:start
many of its secrets
from mankind.

00:22:25.112 --> 00:22:27.748 position:7% line:89% align:start
Bearing 110, take her to base.

00:22:27.782 --> 00:22:29.449 position:44% line:89% align:start
Aye.

00:22:29.482 --> 00:22:33.054 position:16% line:89% align:start
[dramatic music playing]

00:22:39.026 --> 00:22:42.830 position:16% line:83% align:start
I've never seen a passage
like that under the ocean.

00:22:42.864 --> 00:22:44.632 position:10% line:83% align:start
We keep secrets from mankind,
too, Jean.

00:22:50.004 --> 00:22:51.505 position:21% line:89% align:start
[awes in fascination]

00:22:56.544 --> 00:22:58.112 position:21% line:89% align:start
We're almost through.

